<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-12-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-12-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="787" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d787">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Bowen</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-12-01"><hi rend="italic">December 1,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hill instructs Mr. Bowen, in case of diplomatic rupture between
                            Germany and Venezuela, to exercise the same good offices for Germany as
                            for Great Britain, with the consent of the Venezuelan Government.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>